    <item>
      <title>Start Vagrant</title>
      <link>/2015/10/15/start-vagrant/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 15 Oct 2015 00:00:00 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/2015/10/15/start-vagrant/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;If you need to run a Vagrant command quickly, check out the commands under &lt;code&gt;SPC
V&lt;/code&gt;. They deal with most of the common commands needed when working with Vagrant
boxes, including tramp SSH. Demonstrated below: &lt;code&gt;vagrant-up&lt;/code&gt; (&lt;code&gt;SPC V V&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You need to have the vagrant layer installed for this to work (&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/syl20bnr/spacemacs/tree/master/layers/+tools/vagrant&#34;&gt;https://github.com/syl20bnr/spacemacs/tree/master/layers/+tools/vagrant&lt;/a&gt;). Add &lt;code&gt;vagrant&lt;/code&gt; to the existing &lt;code&gt;dotspacemacs-configuration-layers&lt;/code&gt; list in your &lt;code&gt;~/.spacemacs&lt;/code&gt; file.&lt;/p&gt;

