    <item>
      <title>Navigate the Filesystem Quickly</title>
      <link>/2015/09/29/navigate-the-filesystem-quickly/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 29 Sep 2015 00:00:00 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/2015/09/29/navigate-the-filesystem-quickly/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;When you need to navigate around your filesystem quickly, hit &lt;code&gt;SPC a d&lt;/code&gt; to open
a &lt;code&gt;dired&lt;/code&gt; buffer in a given directory (you&amp;rsquo;ll be able to specify it.) Once
you&amp;rsquo;re in, hit &lt;code&gt;enter&lt;/code&gt; to open a file or directory, and dthe normal movement
keys to navigate. You can hit &lt;code&gt;?&lt;/code&gt; to get a list of other keybindings for doing
things like deleting, renaming, and copying files. A cool thing to note is that
if you rename a file using &lt;code&gt;dired&lt;/code&gt;, the associated buffers open in emacs will
also be renamed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;gfyitem&#34; data-autoplay=true data-controls=true data-expand=true data-id=&#34;KaleidoscopicObedientGecko&#34; &gt;&lt;/div&gt;
