    <item>
      <title>Jump to any line in a buffer</title>
      <link>/2015/09/17/jump-to-any-line-in-a-buffer/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 17 Sep 2015 00:00:00 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/2015/09/17/jump-to-any-line-in-a-buffer/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You can jump to any line in a buffer with &lt;code&gt;evil-ace-jump-line-mode&lt;/code&gt; (&lt;code&gt;SPC l&lt;/code&gt;).
Hit the shortcut and then the letter of a line in the popup and you&amp;rsquo;ll go there.
You can get back quickly with &lt;code&gt;SPC `&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;gfyitem&#34; data-autoplay=true data-controls=true data-expand=true data-id=&#34;FaintThriftyAlligator&#34; &gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note: as of this writing the function on this key is &lt;code&gt;evil-ace-jump-line-mode&lt;/code&gt;,
but it &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/syl20bnr/spacemacs/pull/2574&#34;&gt;will be changing&lt;/a&gt; to
&lt;code&gt;avy-goto-line&lt;/code&gt; in the next release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update February 2016&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;code&gt;SPC l&lt;/code&gt; is now the new layouts engine. This
functionality is now located at &lt;code&gt;SPC y&lt;/code&gt;. Thanks Caolite O&amp;rsquo;Connor for the catch!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;

